==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tike
<hw>Tike</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
tick. See 2d <er>Tick</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tike</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tike
<hw>Tike</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>t⟦imac⟧k</ets> a bitch;
akin to Sw. <ets>tik</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dog; a cur.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Bobtail <xex>tike</xex> or trundle-tail.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A countryman or clown; a boorish, clumsy, or
eccentric person; -- also spelled <asp>tyke</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a small child; -- variant of
<er>tyke</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tikor</ent>⟦br⟧
